alert.note: Alert for Palm Beach (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 25 at 4:19PM EDT until May 25 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Miami
info.description: The National Weather Service in Miami has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Northeastern Palm Beach County in southeastern Florida... * Until 445 PM EDT. * At 419 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Golden Lakes, or near West Palm Beach, moving northeast at 10 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... West Palm Beach, Wellington, Palm Beach Gardens, Lake Worth and Riviera Beach. HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building.
